        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 12:34AM PDT by NWS Spokane WA</headline>
        <description>At 1233 AM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southeast of Nordman, or 20 miles northwest of Sandpoint,
moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Coolin.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
